The paper deals with structural parameters of graphs and their use in obtaining efficient algorithms, which is a common theme in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Combinatorics (cs.DM). The concept of rank-width, which is a key focus of the paper, is also closely related to the study of graph decompositions and algorithms for solving problems on decomposed graphs, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of modulators in solving problems such as Minimum Vertex Cover and Maximum Clique, which are classic problems in Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Graph Theory (cs.CG). Finally, the paper introduces an algorithmic meta-theorem for deciding problems expressible in Monadic Second Order (MSO) logic, which is a topic in Logic in Computer Science (cs.LG).
